-- Diagnostic: why build-l findings don't match any root --
  `_finding_mentions_path` reads primary_file, evidence list, and summary.
  Scorer-shape AUDIT_REPORT.json stores path info in the raw `file` +
  `description` keys, which `AuditFinding.from_dict` does NOT map to
  `evidence`. Only `title` -> summary survives, and summary text is a
  one-liner that rarely includes a full canonical path.

  Consequence: against scorer-shape raw input, N-11 collapse rate is 0.
  Flag-OFF is byte-identical (confirmed). Flag-ON only meaningfully
  collapses when upstream findings already carry path info in
  `evidence[]` or when summary contains the canonical path literal.

